<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1427,2036]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1427,1452]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
R 
<number box="[303,311,1442,1456]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[320,327,1442,1456]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
complete at base; r-m present; arm of gonocoxite sinuous, apically with many short and thick bristles; two pairs of projections in the aedeagal complex, the subtriangular dorsal with sharp apex; the ventral, with sharp apex, longer than the dorsal projection, jointed apically by a ventral membrane; ejaculatory apodeme twice the length of gonostylus; cercus with a projection with two apical bristles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1427,2036]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,424,1573,1598]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Head subcircular in frontal view. Antenna: scape subcylindrical about as long as the subspherical pedicel; flagellum with 
<number box="[598,626,1613,1637]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="13.0">13</number>
flagellomeres, 
<number box="[816,830,1613,1637]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
st to 
<number box="[893,921,1613,1637]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="12.0">12</number>
th pyriforms and eccentric (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1368,1612,1637]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1315,1345,1613,1637]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
A
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[1396,1424,1613,1637]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="13.0">13</number>
th flagellomere subcylindrical with terminal apiculus separated by suture (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1109,1648,1673]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1058,1088,1649,1673]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
C
</figureCitation>
); pair of digitiform ascoids present in all flagellomeres; basal ascoids 
<number box="[633,717,1685,1709]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4</number>
times the length of flagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1214,1684,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1161,1191,1685,1709]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
A
</figureCitation>
); apical ascoids 
<number box="[1401,1436,1685,1709]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times the length of flagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[524,627,1720,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[576,607,1721,1745]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
C
</figureCitation>
). Palpus three segmented; first segment with sensilla in depressed pit on medial surface; palpus formula 1.0: 
<number box="[548,586,1757,1781]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="0.7">0.7</number>
: 
<number box="[590,628,1757,1781]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="0.8">0.8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[645,748,1756,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[697,728,1757,1781]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
B
</figureCitation>
). Wing. R 
<number box="[862,870,1771,1785]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[879,886,1771,1785]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
complete at base; r-m present; m-cu absent (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,181,1796,1820]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
D
</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia: Hypandrium fused with gonocoxites narrow. Gonocoxites with posterior sinuous arm, apically with many short and thick bristles. Gonostylus articulated ventrally to gonocoxite, digitiform, bare. Two pairs of projections in the aedeagal complex, the first dorsal pair, subtriangular, with sharp apex and directed to the midline; the second pair of projections, ventral, complex, with sharp apex, longer than the dorsal projections, jointed apically by a ventral membrane. Aedeagus short (
<figureCitation box="[827,936,1939,1964]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[884,914,1940,1964]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
H
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme twice the length of gonostylus. Epandrium subrectangular (
<figureCitation box="[612,796,1975,2000]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Figs. 
<number box="[680,709,1976,2000]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
E, 
<number box="[744,774,1976,2000]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
G
</figureCitation>
). Cercus bottle-shaped in lateral view with two apical bristles (
<figureCitation box="[247,348,2011,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[299,329,2012,2036]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
F
</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct with apical micropilosity (
<figureCitation box="[788,890,2011,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 A – H" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,411,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[151,1435,411,1855]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 28 A – H. Trichomyia hispida sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Last flagellomere; D. Left wing; E. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; F. Cercus, lateral; G. Male terminalia, lateral; H. Male terminalia, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262745/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[841,871,2012,2036]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
E
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
